// Polymorphism 

it means many form poly means many , morph means many .
Java one entity can makes many form means same methods or object can behave differently.

Types of polymorphism -> A. Method overloading ->
Achieved when multiple methods have the same name but different parameters. The method call is resolved at compile time.

B.Method overriding-> 
Achieved when a subclass provides a specific implementation of a method already defined in its superclass. 
The method call is resolved at runtime based on the object

